goal.en:
This text discusses the significant societal changes brought about by science, technology, and artificial intelligence (AI). These advancements impact not just a single field, but cross-disciplinary transformations and innovations. The development of science, technology, and AI has also sparked many discussions about gender-related issues. “Gendered Innovations“ encourages incorporating gender perspectives into the development of technology and AI, thereby fostering innovation in both technology and gender.

There are two key aspects to technology‘s desire for gender inclusivity: first, understanding the parts of scientific, technological, and AI development related to gender, including potential biases and controversies in their application processes; and second, combining technology and gender to develop innovative solutions and perspectives for addressing problems.

This course explores the interconnections between gender, technology, and society through the lenses of AI knowledge production, AI use and policy, and AI representation. It aims to employ the “Gendered Innovations“ approach to identify and solve existing problems by introducing innovative methods. The course seeks to foster cross-disciplinary dialogue on gender and technology, guiding gender-based innovations in technological development and improving existing gender-based exclusions and disadvantages in social structures. 

The course will focus on gender issues in the application of technology and AI, discussing its application and innovation across various fields, and ultimately creating possibilities for gender innovations in social development. It has four main learning objectives: 
1. Understanding perspectives on technology, AI development, and gender studies;
2. Understanding the interaction between technology and gender;
3. Mastering the content of key issues; 
4. Rethinking the relationship between technology, AI, and gender, along with their creative potential.
